The paper discusses the implementation of Binarized Neural Networks using resistive memory technologies, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The use of neural networks also suggests the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the design and optimization of memory arrays, which falls under the category of Architecture (cs.AR) and Electronics Materials (cs.EM). Finally, the paper presents results on machine learning tasks, which suggests the category of Machine Learning (cs.MA).
